newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Australian sugar crush - week to Nov 16.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Australian sugar crush - week to Nov 16.

text.p: Australia's sugar cane crush totalled 1.340 million tonnes in the week ended November 16, down from 1.440 million tonnes in the previous week, grower organisation CANEGROWERS said.
CANEGROWERS reported for crushing week 24 of the 1996 season that average commercial cane sugar (ccs) content fell to 13.50 percent from 13.53 percent the week before.
The latest week brought this year's crush to 36.86 million tonnes, up from 33.41 million tonnes at the same time in 1995.
Australian sugar cane crush by region for the week ended November 16 as reported by CANEGROWERS in tonnes.
The 1995 crush started on June 13 and ended by December 30.
CCS = Commercial Cane Sugar (sugar content percent)-

1995 Summary - Total cane crushed 37.389 million tonnes (Qld 35.295 million, NSW 2.094 million), sugar produced 4.98 million tonnes 94 n.t., (Qld 4.73 million, NSW 244,629), sugar content (CCS) 13.12 percent (Qld 13.22 percent, NSW 11.41 percent).
